Folio in sixes. Title‚ Preface of Toxites, privilegium, Preface of Paracelsus: in all ff. 16, not numbered. Text ff. 165.

Colophon on f. [166]: Gedruckt zu Franckfurt am Mayn, bey Martin Lechler, in verlegung Hieronymi Feyerabends. Anno M.D.LXXI.

The title as given by Mook (No. 91) is a travesty of the original. He omits the word teutschen before Philosophi, and the whole passage beginning Darium er lellrt down to wira-ken, etc. He also omits from Sigismvndvs to the end of the date, instead -of which he inserts the colophon (omit- ting the date) as isit formed part of the title.

The reason for these changes is to me quite unapparent, especially as it is a chief complaint against other cataloguers by Mook (p. 21) that their titles are defective.
